Jeff,

The current project fits within the FERC's new regulations under the Automatic Blanket requirements since the project scope is to build a new delivery point, potential branchline and costs will not exceed the current authorized level of $7.3 million and is not a by-pass of an existing customer.  There are several issues that need to be completed before construction can begin:  An executed transportation contract, Landowner notification and Environmental clearances.  Please keep us informed as the project progresses to make sure all the FERC requirements are met before the construction begins.  

